The paper deals with hyperspectral signature classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of statistical models to characterize wavelet coefficients is a machine learning approach (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with extracting features from hyperspectral signatures. The use of hidden Markov chain models is a signal processing technique (cs.DS) that is commonly used in machine learning. Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses statistical models to classify hyperspectral signatures.
